        typeof(val0) __val0 = (val0);                           \

static int ostid_to_fid ( struct lu_fid *  fid,
const struct ost_id *  ostid,
__u32  ost_idx 
) [inline, static]

Unpack an OST object id/seq (group) into a FID.

This is needed for converting all obdo, lmm, lsm, etc. 64-bit id/seq pairs into proper FIDs. Note that if an id/seq is already in FID/IDIF format it will be passed through unchanged. Only legacy OST objects in "group 0" will be mapped into the IDIF namespace so that they can fit into the struct lu_fid fields without loss. For reference see: http://arch.lustre.org/index.php?title=Interoperability_fids_zfs
